messages.body_plain:
Some of the function names are misspelled (e.g. Rf_iisNull instead of
Rf_isNull) in WRE in R 4.5.2 and R-devel. This patch fixes them.

Duncan Murdoch

Index: doc/manual/R-exts.texi
===================================================================
--- doc/manual/R-exts.texi (revision 89432)
+++ doc/manual/R-exts.texi (working copy)
@@ -12833,8 +12833,8 @@
@apifun Rf_isInteger
@apifun Rf_isString
Other such functions declared in the header file @file{Rinternals.h}
-include @code{Rf_iisNull}, @code{Rf_iisSymbol}, @code{Rf_iisLogical},
- at code{Rf_iisComplex}, @code{Rf_iisExpression}, and
@code{Rf_iisEnvironment}.
+include @code{Rf_isNull}, @code{Rf_isSymbol}, @code{Rf_isLogical},
+ at code{Rf_isComplex}, @code{Rf_isExpression}, and @code{Rf_isEnvironment}.
@apifun Rf_isNull
@apifun Rf_isSymbol
@apifun Rf_isLogical

